1 Introduction

The objective of this analysis is to build interactive visualizations of predicted crime hotspots, actual crime behaviour and the predictors in Raleigh, North Carolina. Due to the large volume of data, we divide the analyses into two maps. One map depicts the hotspots together with demographic predictors. The second map depicts the hotspots together with points of interest predictors and all predicted crime in the city.

2 Configuration and File Import

The model output was pre-generated. We will load the Models for the 2020 test period. Base date is 2019-12-31.
